## Tracing and logging

OpenTelemetry Trace Context is enabled by default in `configs/local.yaml`; OTLP export is disabled until an endpoint is explicitly configured. HTTP and gRPC propagate W3C `traceparent`, HTTP responses include `X-Trace-ID`, and application shutdown flushes tracing after servers stop.

Use structured context-aware logs so trace correlation fields are attached automatically:

```go
logx.InfoCtx(ctx, "operation completed", "key", value)
logx.ErrorCtx(ctx, "operation failed", "key", value, "err", err)
```
